CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 6, 1954, pg. 2, reads: "'Agent of the Week' - Debit Manager Floyd M. Hall, right ,is sown receiving congratulations from Bradford E. Williams, Pittsburgh district manager of the Supreme Liberty Life Insurance Company, upon being designated as 'Agent of the Week.' Mr. Hall is the newest addition to the staff and has maintained a high average in hospital production, and this week topped it off with $8,500 ordinary production. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Floyd M. Hall pointing to chalkboard inscribed "Agent of the week! Hosp $3.85! Ordinary $8,500!" in Supreme Liberty Life Insurance Company
